<h2>Resource Action</h2>
<p>
    Manages the async mutation lifecycle (POST/PUT/DELETE) &mdash; busy state on triggers, double-submit prevention,
    optimistic updates with automatic rollback on error. The complement to <a href="/blocks/resource-loader/">Resource Loader</a>
    (which handles reads); Resource Action handles writes.
    Part of the <a href="/projects/webresources/">Web Resources</a> ecosystem.
</p>

<h3>Architecture: Reads vs Writes</h3>
<p>
    Reads and writes have fundamentally different UX patterns. <a href="/blocks/resource-loader/">Resource Loader</a> shows
    loading states <strong>in-place</strong> (skeletons, overlays, stale content). Resource Action shows busy states
    <strong>on triggers</strong> (disabled buttons, spinners, width locking) and delivers feedback (toasts, revert).
</p>
<table>
    <thead>
        <tr><th></th><th>Resource Loader (Reads)</th><th>Resource Action (Writes)</th></tr>
    </thead>
    <tbody>
        <tr>
            <td><strong>Trigger</strong></td>
            <td>Navigation, mount, focus/reconnect</td>
            <td>User click, form submit, command</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
            <td><strong>Loading UX</strong></td>
            <td>In-place: skeleton, overlay, stale content</td>
            <td>On trigger: busy button, disabled state</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
            <td><strong>Success UX</strong></td>
            <td>Content replaces loading state</td>
            <td>Toast notification, cache invalidation</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
            <td><strong>Error UX</strong></td>
            <td>Error card replaces content</td>
            <td>Toast/alert, optimistic revert</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
            <td><strong>Cancellation</strong></td>
            <td>Navigation supersede (automatic)</td>
            <td>User-initiated or timeout</td>
        </tr>
    </tbody>
</table>

<h3>Web Standards Alignment</h3>
<table>
    <tr><th>Standard</th><th>Status</th><th>How We Adopt It</th></tr>
    <tr>
        <td><a href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/API/Fetch_API">Fetch API</a></td>
